This paper deals with the Leiden Rankings, which are a measure of research output and impact of universities. The paper focuses on statistical significance and effect sizes of differences among universities in different countries, which involves data analysis and statistical methods. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), which deals with the organization, retrieval, and distribution of digital information. Other likely categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.SD (Software Development).
